Heat oil in medium saucepan over medium heat. Add onion; cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until onion begins to soften. Add rice; cook and stir 2 minutes. Add broth; bring to boiling. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer uncovered 15 minutes. Add peas and water, if rice has absorbed all liquid. Reduce heat to low and cook covered 5 minutes. Remove from heat; let stand covered 5 minutes. Stir in seafood butter. Season to taste with salt and pepper.